評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["Contemporary Topics 2 (Supplementary materials will be provided by the instructor whenever needed.)Students are encouraged to bring a dictionary to class."], "教科書/Required texts1": ["Ellen Kisslinger", "Contemporary Topics 2 (4th Edition)", "Pearson Education, Inc.", "2017 年", "9780134400808", ""], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students0": ["Students will independently evaluate the instructor and the course at the end of the semester.&nbsp;"], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["その他／Others (99)", "100 %", "Students’ final grades will derive from a combination of assignments, activities, presentations, mini tests, etc."], "成績評価Grading2": ["備考　Note 1. Active participation is extremely important and counts as a significant part of students’ evaluation marks.&nbsp;&nbsp;2. Attendance is crucial to students’ success in this course. The instructor will carefully mark students’ attendance as&nbsp;present and on time, late,&nbsp;or&nbsp;absent.&nbsp;Specific rules regarding attendance are as follows:&nbsp;2a) Only students who are present at the time the class begins will receive full attendance marks.&nbsp;2b) Any student walking into the classroom after the class has begun will be marked late. The instructor will take this into account when giving students a participation grade.2c) Being 15 to 29 minutes late will equal half an absence (0.5).&nbsp;2d) Each time students are late 30 minutes or&nbsp;more, they will be marked&nbsp;absent.&nbsp;However, they are still encouraged to attend.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2e) No more than three absences will be permitted in this course. Any student who is absent more than three&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;times will automatically fail this course."], "備考Note0": ["In principle, the use of smartphones, tablets, and other electronic devices in the classroom is forbidden. Students must store them in their bags throughout the entire duration of each class.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the case of a project in which internet connection is necessary, the instructor may instruct students to use their electronic devices, but unless such a situation is specifically and clearly suggested by the instructor, their use will be strictly prohibited."], "備考Note1": ["2026年03月04日 13時18分50秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "火曜３時限／Tuesday 3", "秋学期／Fall", "Ｈ－３０２"]}, "campas": 0, "name": "【100】English Communication Ｄ　２／English Communication D", "管理部署": 2, "単位数": 1, "担当者": "カバリ　ヴィヴィアン（KHAVARI VIVIAN BUSSINGUER） ", "履修基準年度": "１年", "履修登録方法": "予備登録", "開講期": 2, "時限1": 9, "評価1": 6, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\n1. Active participation is extremely important and counts as a significant part of students’ evaluation marks.  \n2. Attendance is crucial to students’ success in this course. The instructor will carefully mark students’ attendance as present and on time, late, or absent. Specific rules regarding attendance are as follows: \n2a) Only students who are present at the time the class begins will receive full attendance marks. \n2b) Any student walking into the classroom after the class has begun will be marked late. The instructor will take this into account when giving students a participation grade.\n2c) Being 15 to 29 minutes late will equal half an absence (0.5). \n2d) Each time students are late 30 minutes or more, they will be marked absent. However, they are still encouraged to attend.  \n             2e) No more than three absences will be permitted in this course. Any student who is absent more than three \n             times will automatically fail this course."}